(<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0003363-t003">Table 3</xref>).</p></sec><sec id="s3f"><title>Adverse events and safety variables</title><p>The number of patients reporting minor or major episodes of hypoglycaemia was not significantly different between treatments (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0003363-t004">Table 4</xref>).</p><table-wrap id="pone-0003363-t004" position="float"><object-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0003363.t004</object-id><label>Table 4</label><caption><title>Reported hypoglycaemic episodes in patients with type-1 diabetes during one year of treatment with metformin or placebo.</title></caption><alternatives><graphic id="pone-0003363-t004-4" xlink:href="pone.0003363.t004"/><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/></colgroup><thead><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Metformin (n&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;49)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Placebo (n&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;50)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">p-value</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
